The system evolves through recursive repetition:

Each cycle updates the model based on prior stability decisions.

Repetition without change leads to equilibrium.
Repetition with controlled variation leads to adaptation.
Uncontrolled variation leads to divergence.

Thus, TERA balances:

persistence

adaptation

stability



